<p><strong>Ordovis's Greatsword</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Greatswords" href="/Greatswords" target="">Greatsword</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Ordovis's Greatsword</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith" target="">Faith</a>. It is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith" target="">Faith</a>&nbsp;builds.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Greatsword of Ordovis, one of the two honored as foremost<br>among the Crucible Knights.</em></p> 
 <p><em>This sword is imbued with an ancient holy essence.<br>Its red tint exemplifies the nature of primordial gold, said to be<br>close in nature to life itself.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Ordovis's Greatsword in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Ordovis's Greatsword weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Dropped by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Crucible Knight Ordovis" href="/Crucible+Knight+Ordovis" target="">Crucible Knight Ordovis</a>, located at <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Auriza Hero's Grave" href="/Auriza+Hero's+Grave" target="">Auriza Hero's Grave</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=2562&amp;lat=-96.85156&amp;lng=122.49704&amp;zoom=8" href="/Interactive+Map?id=2562&amp;lat=-96.85156&amp;lng=122.49704&amp;zoom=8">Elden Ring Map here</a>].</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Ordovis's Greatsword Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ordovis's Vortex" href="/Ordovis's+Vortex" target="">Ordovis's Vortex</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li>Can't be enchanted with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;nor boosted by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</li> 
 <li><strong>Ordovis's Greatsword</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a>.</li> 
 <li>Decent&nbsp;on a Strength&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Builds" href="/Builds" target="">Builds</a>,&nbsp;as it mainly scales to&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>, Faith and Dex can be req only.</li> 
 <li>The skill also scales to AR, not to Faith. Since both Dex and Faith Scaling on this weapon are terrible, rushing to 80 STR is the best option to maximise damage on both regular attacks and the skill.</li> 
 <li>The Vortex is slow, meaning you'll need either proper timing or high poise to pull off a full charge. It has an AOE so can take out multiple enemies, and when you slam it into the ground it has a ripple effect depending on how much Vortex was charged. These ripples each due rapid damage that quickly stacks up, and they cause enemies to stagger on each one. If you're quick with a heavy follow up, you can cause a stance break.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;1000</li> 
 <li>Vortex deals both Physical and Holy Damage, though much more Physical than Holy (~80%).</li> 
 <li>As a chargable weapon skill, the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Godfrey Icon" href="/Godfrey+Icon" target="">Godfrey Icon</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Shard of Alexander" href="/Shard+of+Alexander" target="">Shard of Alexander</a> will both increase the damage of the Vortex.</li> 
 <li>Vortex grants a good amount of Poise, making it hard to interrupt</li> 
 <li>Like most weapons that deal multiple damage types, this weapon has increased AR to compensate for the fact that its damage is calculated against two different enemy resistances (standard or pierce, and holy in this case).</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
